narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I developed a thorough understanding of some of the basic rhetorical techniques that make for college-level writing. Also, I gained a cursory understanding of how to research a topic using Yales wealth of resources. This class definitely made me a better writer.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: well-organized and you know what to expect, helpful ways to receive feedback, peer reviews, etc.
Weaknesses: sometimes too forumlaic and the readings got a bit too abstract and theoretical for my taste; sometimes topics were detached from students lives.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! This course was really good in improving my ability to read difficult essays and discuss them with others.
Yes I definitely would recommended this course for anyone looking to improve their writing and reading skills.
